cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the task of white-matter lesion segmentation in brain MR scans, which is a problem in computer vision and medical imaging. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of ensemble-nets and a novel activation function could indicate a focus on optimization and neural network architecture, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of medical imaging data could suggest a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia).
